-- Lifan Industry Shanghai Initial Public Offering Approved by Regulator
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-18T01:00:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/lifan-industry-shanghai-initial-public-offering-approved-by-regulator.html
Lifan Industry Group Co., which
American International Group owns a stake in, won approval from
the China Securities Regulatory Commission to list in Shanghai,
according to a statement posted to the regulator’s website on
Oct. 15.  The Chongqing-based automaker plans to raise 1.48 billion
yuan through the initial public offering, according to a
prospectus on the CSRC’s website. AIG owns a 13.5 percent stake
in Lifan through a unit called Join State Ltd., the prospectus
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  